TS Galaxy have completed a shock signing of a major signing that will stand as the marquee acquisition of this transfer window. TS Galaxy have confirmed the club big signing so far in the current Premier Soccer League transfer period. The Rockets announced the signing of Xola Mlambo on Thursday morning. On the same day afternoon, The Rockets pulled another surprise out of the bag when they revealed that they have signed former Mamelodi Sundowns midfielder Sibusiso Vilakazi. The club did not divulge much on the arrival of Vilakazi as they just tweeted a brief statement welcoming the player. “TS Galaxy FC has completed the signing of Sibusiso "Villa" Vilakazi. Welcome to the Rockets Family Villa,” said the club. Vilakazi spent the past six years at Mamelodi Sundowns winning five league titles, two Nedbank Cups, Telkom Knockout, MTN8, and CAF Super Cup in 2016 CAF Champions League was also won when he was already at the club. Vila’s move to Galaxtcame as a huge shock as he was linked with a move to Kaizer Chiefs. TS Galaxy FC has completed the signing of Sibusiso "Villa" Vilakazi. Welcome to the Rockets Family Villa.#Siyadumuza #TheRockets #TSG #WeAreHereToStay pic.twitter.com/OxLvAAaStb   